               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors (erased); the words sälam “salutation” and hale luya in Text I-1a, elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements.&#xD;
&#xD;
Several groups of lines on the incipit page of Texts I-1a, I-1b, I-3b, I-4, I-5 and I-6, alternating with black lines; several groups of lines in the incipit of Text I-2, alternating with black lines; two initial lines in the incipit of Text I-3a; groups of lines on the incipit page of sections of Texts I-1b and I-3a alternating with black lines; two initial lines of the sections of Texts I-1a and I-4 (sometimes alternating with black lines) and its section numbers; first word of each strophe of Text I-5.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The miracles of St. Mary (Text I-4) are numbered.</note>
                     <note>Text I-5 comprises 33 strophes which are strophes 1-31, 33-34 according to GrohHymn pp. 336-53.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-5 is followed by a subscriptio stating the number of stophes of Text I-5 (33) and of the miracles of Text I-4 (134): ተፈጸመ፡ በዝየ፡ ተአምሪሃ፡ ለማርያም፡ ዝውእቱ፡ አኮኑ፡ ብእሲ፡ ፴፫፡ ወኵሉ፡ ድሙር፡ ፻ወ፴፬። …</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus/>Fols. 181va-182ra: ተፈጸመት፡ ዘቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ በ፪፻ወ፶፡ ዓመተ ምሕረት፡ &lt;…&gt;በመዋዕሊሆሙ፡ &lt;…&gt; ዘነበረ፡ እንዘ፡ ይብል፡ … <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                        <note>Several lines of the extensive colophon have been erased. The writing of the Ms. was completed in 250 year of mercy (= 1598 A.D. or 1674 A.D., cp. ChChron 166,167).</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
